      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that but my doctor is super hard to reach and i can't wait until monday to find out. i'm just looking at my CGM and it's sitting around 110 right now. if i take the full dose on top of a tiny salad it feels like i'll definitely go low overnight. shouldn't i just be able to scale it back or skip it if my glucose is already stable? it just seems more logical to adjust based on what i actually ate.",
