      "content": "Understanding that you're seeking to adapt your insulin dosing based on your dietary intake is important, but it's crucial to do so under professional guidance. Sudden changes without medical supervision can be dangerous. Your current reading of 110 mg/dL suggests a stable level, but insulin adjustments should not be made based on short-term readings or without consulting your healthcare team. It's best to reach out to your provider as soon as possible, even if it's through a nurse line or shared care service they provide. Plan an alternative or ask if a pre-carbohydrate snack could help stabilize your levels until you can speak to your doctor. Your well-being is of utmost importance.",
